Moms w/ double digit kiddos, teens + adult kids y’all okay? Ooo how about the moms with teens AND three-nagers?? 😭😂

So with this check in I wanted to share 5 lessons i’ve learned while raising a teen…k?

1. Patience will come in different forms. No more needy toddler = less patience and less “mess ups”?? Nope, quite the opposite. Teens have a lot that they’re navigating through. They too lack some maturity skills and you have to learn not to sweat the small stuff. “Patience is when you’re supposed to get mad, but you choose to understand.” But that’s just me. 

2. Work through your projections. How you were raised will need some tweaking when it comes to how you raise and parent your big kiddo. Watch what you criticize even if you think it’s constructive. Sometimes you have to JUST listen and hold the lecture. Different person, different times. They’re their own person. But that’s just me. 

3. Show your human side. Always concealing when you’re angry, or hurt, or emotional or whatever is not always the best way. Apologize when you’re wrong, take accountability and let them know how you used to be in these streeeeeeeets. Pray about the last one cus i’m not you and you ain’t me. I talk talk to my teen. But that’s just me. 

4. Talk about relationships, sex all that. Be open and be honest no matter how uncomfortable it may be. BE SO FORREAL. Sugar coating never worked for me bc life is short lol. Your teen needs and deserves honesty. But that’s just me. 

5. Don’t take everything so personal. We all have bad days. And if you have a teen DAUGHTER, you already know lol. Cus I can just breathe one day and that will annoy her lol. But grace is key. You used to be a teen, you know what it is. Times are different. It comes with teen hood. But that’s just me. 
6. Bonus - you’re an AMAZING MOM!!!! 

I try to check in with this small community of mamas with big kiddos, teens and adult kids, bc we can be often overlooked. Our connection always reminds me to make sure we have a space to share how we’re navigating the ghe…I mean this side of parenting. I’m just tryna be the BEST mama to my baby, she deserves that and so much more. 🫶🏽 #MomOfATeen #GirlMom #MomLife
I CAN’T HELP IT.

The baby went to homecoming over the weekend and let me tell you something…I STAN!!!!!

Ok so, i’ve mentioned before that when she was little I made the decision not to straighten her hair for special occasions and instead we did natural hairstyles for everything no matter how regular or how special. That was my personal decision and i’m not knocking anyone who does the opposite 🫶🏽

I grew up feeling like my hair wasn’t beautiful unless it was BONE straight. I begged my mom for a relaxer at 8 years old and homegirl said absolutely not lol. I hid my texture for years and ultimately damaged my hair over time. It was important for me that my kid knew all of this, my personal struggles surrounding my hair and how I grew to love my natural curls and etc. Plus since I’m a natural hair content creator, it was also imperative to me that she not only heard me but saw me. Ultimately, I wanted her to understand that although she had the option to, she didn’t need to straighten her hair just because she was getting dressed up or to feel beautiful. 

As we were approaching the date sis said “I wanna wear my fro to homecoming” and i can’t even deal at how she ATE it UP 😍😍😍!!!! Like, wow…i can stare at my baby all day - pure perfection. AND her daddy fine and does NOT play about his daughter either. 😂

Mom + dad dropped her off, went on a little casual date, did some shopping and fell asleep in the car waiting while she danced the night away. Still crazy that we have a whole teenager, but we couldn’t be more proud of the beautiful person she is 😭😭 #MomOfATeen #GirlMom #Naturalhair #NaturalHairTeens

I’ll forever be a wash and go girl. We know, lol. However, the product junkie in me has left the building and she’s been gone for a very long…periodically time…and i love that for me. Picking three products was easy, and they’ve all shown up consistently: 

- @ilovethedoux bee girl honey custard *closes eyes slowly* is MY GO TO. I buy a jar even if I have a full one at the house 😂. I wash my hair every 3-4 days but, if I wanted to, I could get 7+ days with just this product. I have a full review and multiple times where i’ve used bee girl on my youtube channel if you want to see more 🙂

- @combat.gel is new to me. More for slick backs, but my wash n go popped, and I was pleasantly surprised. It’s all I have in my 5th day hair in this video and she’s been through workouts, saunas + wind and not a flake in sight. It was hard to get online bc it’s always sold out, but worth the wait. 

- @patternbeauty curl mousse has been that gworl. Mousse was never my friend, until recently. Pattern’s curl mousse gives you a “soft” hold that lasts. And I don’t do soft holdssss, however, my hair loves this stuff. My wash and go’s come out light, but shiny and defined. This is probably my 5th bottle purchased, i’ve lost track. A staple!

It’s finally freezing in LA hitting 70 degrees and what not + me and the ppl I live with finally decided to make our way downtown walking fast faces pass to the @packingdistrict in Anaheim, CA last week!
